Write a program that gets n as input and print the reverse of the number

Testcase 1 :

Input : 

325345

Expected output:

543523



Testcase 2 :

Input : 

987987

Expected output:

789789


program:
import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Scanner S=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=S.nextInt();
        while(n>0){
            int ld=n%10;
            n=n/10;
            System.out.print(ld);
        }
    }
}
